{
  "stem": "24171.7",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were so happy that we have a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's a thing that's--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] No, that through the letter--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A contact.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, things.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went-- after the war, we went to [NON-ENGLISH], you know, in the Sudeten.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was in November.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was Hanukka, when we arrived there, by the time-- you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know how long it took, a week, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I really-- Hanukkah comes out always in different, according to Yiddish or the Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in November, the 24th.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we went there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there, the-- was in around-- it came up [NON-ENGLISH] time, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In March, they started talking that the Russians are going to take over the whole Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So in April-- and then, my husband went to Prague to find out from other people-- I have cousins in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, in every city there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he went to Prague there and to find out what's going on, to hear some more news about that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they said, yeah, definitely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on the first of May, they have, the communists, a big celebration.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so, by then, he came home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he started packing again, fixing up again the knapsacks and suitcases, and left everything there on the floor again, because we had already some, we found something there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We got kind of established in those-- during the winter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Barry had his-- my husband had his two sisters with him, and a brother, David, [INAUDIBLE], if you want to know him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of the sisters got married there, in [NON-ENGLISH] there, where my [? brother-in-law ?] were living.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so there we were again on the road.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
